---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About">
  <section class="hero-gradient" style="color: white; padding: 3rem 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; opacity: 0.75; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">About</p>
      <h1 style="color: white; margin: 0;">Hi, I'm Sunny Venkatesh</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container page-section">
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 2rem; align-items: start; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <div class="avatar" style="width: 80px; height: 80px; font-size: 2rem; flex-shrink: 0;">S</div>
      <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 280px;">
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">Why I built this</h2>
        <p>
          I've been researching neuroplastic pain for a while — both out of personal experience
          and genuine curiosity about how the brain processes pain. What I found surprised me:
          the research is clear, rigorous, and hopeful. But it's scattered across dense academic
          journals and behind paywalls.
        </p>
        <p>
          Pain Rewired is my attempt to bridge that gap. I use AI-assisted summarization to
          translate the latest peer-reviewed research into plain language, then curate and
          review everything before it goes live. The result is a free, accessible resource
          for anyone trying to understand their chronic pain.
        </p>

        <h2>How it works</h2>
        <p>
          Every week, a pipeline I built searches PubMed and relevant blogs for new papers on
          neuroplastic pain, central sensitization, and related topics. Each paper is summarized
          using AI (Gemini 1.5 Flash), then I review and publish the most relevant ones.
        </p>
        <p>
          The intro guides, glossary, quiz, and resources were all hand-crafted to give you
          a solid foundation without needing a medical degree.
        </p>

        <h2>Get in touch</h2>
        <p>
          I'd love to hear from you — corrections, suggestions, or just to say hi.
        </p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <a href="https://in.linkedin.com/in/sunny-venkatesh-877896194" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-primary">
            Connect on LinkedIn →
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="margin-top: 2rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--accent); background: var(--accent-light);">
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
            <strong>Important:</strong> I'm not a doctor or medical professional. The content on
            this site is for educational purposes only. Always consult a healthcare provider
            for medical advice. This site reflects my personal research journey.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
